The paper discusses the use of social media data for social science research and journalism, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). The paper also describes the design decisions made in developing a system for collecting and analyzing political discourse on Twitter, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the visualization of large amounts of data, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
